  "A winemaker uses cold stabilization to prevent tartrate crystals from forming in bottled wine. She chills the wine to near 0°C for several weeks. Clear crystals settle to the bottom and are removed by filtration. What principle of separation is used, and why must this be done before bottling?": "",
